column15: MethodDescription: Air temperature measured using a Campbell Scientific HC2S3 temperature and relative humidity sensor. Average over 15 minutes.
MethodDescription: Relative humidity measured using a Campbell Scientific HC2S3 temperature and relative humidity sensor.
MethodDescription: Dew point temperature measured using a Campbell Scientific CS210 relative humidity sensor.
MethodDescription: Vapor pressure measured using a Campbell Scientific CS210 relative humidity sensor.
MethodDescription: Barometric pressure measured using a Campbell Scientific CS106 barometric pressure sensor.
MethodDescription: Wind speed measured using a RM Young 05103-45 anemometer and vane. Average over 15 minutes.
MethodDescription: Wind direction measured using a RM Young 05103-45 anemometer and vane.
MethodDescription: Wind direction measured using a RM Young 05103-45 anemometer and vane.
MethodDescription: Precipitation measured using a Geonor T-200B rain gage. Average of 6 readings in the final minute prior to reporting.

MethodDescription: Frequency of vibration of the wire supporting the precipitation collector of the Geonor T-200B rain gage. Used to determine precipitation volume. Average of 6 readings in the final minute prior to reporting.
MethodDescription: Snow depth measured using a Judd snow sensor. Calculated as the average of six measurements with outliers (>90% of the offset or <10) excluded.
MethodDescription: Air temperature measured using a Judd snow sensor.
MethodDescription: Incoming shortwave radiation measured using a Huskeflux NR01 radiometer.
MethodDescription: Outgoing shortwave radiation measured using a Huskeflux NR01 radiometer.
MethodDescription: Incoming longwave radiation measured using a Huskeflux NR01 radiometer. Values are corrected for temperature.
MethodDescription: Outgoing longwave radiation measured using a Huskeflux NR01 radiometer. Values are corrected for temperature.

MethodDescription: Net radiation determined by the difference between Incoming(Shortwave + Longwave) and Outgoing (Shortwave + Longwave). All quantities measured by the Huskeflux NR01 radiometer and corrected for temperature.
MethodDescription: Incoming longwave radiation measured using a Huskeflux NR01 radiometer. Values are not corrected for temperature.
MethodDescription: Outgoing longwave radiation measured using a Huskeflux NR01 radiometer. Values are not corrected for temperature.
MethodDescription: Sensor body temperature of the Huskeflux NR01 radiometer.
MethodDescription: Incoming shortwave radiation measured using an Apogee SP-230 pyranometer.
MethodDescription: Indicator as to whether the heater is on or off.

MethodDescription: Temperature difference between the Huskeflux NR01 sensor body temperature and the dew point temperature measured by the Campbell Scientific CS210 sensor. When the temperature difference is less than 1 deg C, the heater is activated.

column7: VariableUnitsName: micromoles per square meter per second
column15: MethodDescription: Incoming photosynthetically active radiation measured by an Apogee SQ-110 sun calibration quantum sensor.

column7: VariableUnitsName: micromoles per square meter per second
column15: MethodDescription: Outgoing photosynthetically active radiation measured by an Apogee SQ-110 sun calibration quantum sensor.

MethodDescription: Temperature of the terrestrial surface measured by the Apogee SI-111 infrared radiometer sensor. Could represent the ground, vegetation, or snow. Determined by constants, sensor body temperature, and sensor voltage output.
MethodDescription: Sensor body temperature of the Apogee SI-111 infrared radiometer sensor. Used to determine the surface temperature.
MethodDescription: Slope for temperature calculation determined by the Apogee SI-111 infrared radiometer sensor. Used to determine the surface temperature.
MethodDescription: Intercept for temperature calculation determined by the Apogee SI-111 infrared radiometer sensor. Used to determine the surface temperature.
MethodDescription: Voltage output of the Apogee SI-111 infrared radiometer sensor. Used to determine the surface temperature.
MethodDescription: Volumetric water content measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 5 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil temperature measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 5 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil conductivity measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 5 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil permittivity measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 5 cm below the water surface. Represents a multiplier on free space permittivity.
MethodDescription: Volumetric water content measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 10 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil temperature measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 10 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil conductivity measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 10 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil permittivity measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 10 cm below the water surface. Represents a multiplier on free space permittivity.
MethodDescription: Volumetric water content measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 20 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil temperature measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 20 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil conductivity measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 20 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil permittivity measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 20 cm below the water surface. Represents a multiplier on free space permittivity.
MethodDescription: Volumetric water content measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 50 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil temperature measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 50 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil conductivity measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 50 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil permittivity measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 50 cm below the water surface. Represents a multiplier on free space permittivity.
MethodDescription: Volumetric water content measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 100 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil temperature measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 100 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil conductivity measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 100 cm below the soil surface.
MethodDescription: Soil permittivity measured using an Acclima Soil Moisture sensor installed 100 cm below the water surface. Represents a multiplier on free space permittivity.
MethodDescription: Battery voltage measured by a Campbell Scientific datalogger.
MethodDescription: Panel temperature measured by a Campbell Scientific datalogger.
MethodDescription: Relative humidity within the station enclosure measured by a Campbell Scientific CS210.
MethodDescription: Indicator of the status of the enclosure door recorded by a Campbell Scientific 18166.
MethodDescription: Counter of the number of scans made within the specified time period recorded by a Campbell Scientific datalogger.
MethodDescription: Offset that reflects the difference between the Judd Snow Sensor and the ground surface. Constant value is manually adjusted to account for sensor drift.
MethodDescription: Air temperature measured using an Apogee ST110 thermistor. Average over 15 minutes.
MethodDescription: Air temperature measured using an Apogee ST110 thermistor. Maximum over 15 minutes.
MethodDescription: Air temperature measured using an Apogee ST110 thermistor. Minimum over 15 minutes.
MethodDescription: Offset that reflects the distance to the baseline for the Geonor precipitation gage.
MethodDescription: The precipitation over the previous hour. Used to determine whether the heater should activate after snowfall.

MethodDescription: Tall grass reference ET determined by the ASCE Standardized Reference Evapotranspiration equation (Etsz in CRBasic). Inputs are air temperature, relative humidity, wind speed, solar radiation, and spatial references.

MethodDescription: Short grass reference ET determined by the ASCE Standardized Reference Evapotranspiration equation (Etsz in CRBasic). Inputs are air temperature, relative humidity, wind speed, solar radiation, and spatial references.
MethodDescription: The inlet temperature of the Geonor precipitation gage.
MethodDescription: Frequency of revolutions of the Apogee TS100 Aspirated Radiation Shield.
MethodDescription: Automated counter to indicate the on/off state of the heater on the Geonor precipitation gage.
MethodDescription: Counter indicating the manual on/off state of the heater on the Geonor precipitation gage.
MethodDescription: Air temperature measured using a Campbell Scientific HC2S3 temperature and relative humidity sensor. Minimum over 15 minutes.
MethodDescription: Air temperature measured using a Campbell Scientific HC2S3 temperature and relative humidity sensor. Maximum over 15 minutes.
MethodDescription: Wind speed measured using a RM Young 05103-45 anemometer and vane. Maximum over 15 minutes.
MethodDescription: Counter of the number of measurements included in the determination of average snow depth (0-6).
